reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent processor with onboard video if you don't want a videocard at present.
reviews.reviewText: Will run most older games no problem. Haven't run any high end new games, but will prob have some lag with max settings. Regardless, this is a fantastic bargain. Blisteringly fast for a basic desktop.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great CPU for folks on a budget
reviews.reviewText: The Ryzen 5 4600G is a good budget choice for several reasons. 1.) It has an integrated GPU so if you don't want to use a GPU, you don't have to. That being said, you're not getting much better than E-Sports with this integrated GPU. But if that's all you're looking for, then it may be up your alley.2.) The price. I got mine for $99 flat and that's a great price full stop. 3.) Compatibility. This chip is compatible with many many AM4 motherboards. 4.) The performance. You should see performance that's only about 5% slower than a Ryzen 5 3600. I think you will have a hard time noticing that in 99% of situations. 5.) It sips power. Right now the max I have seen it use a max of 39 watts, and that's at 100% load. So I'm not sure if I need to put it under some sort of synthetic load or something to get it to hit 65W, but it's been really awesome so far.I recommend this processor wholeheartedly for people on a budget. If you can afford a 5600, the 5600X or higher, you should get it since they are faster, have more cache, and support things like PCI Express 4.0. But overall just a really good processor for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Need for speed!
reviews.reviewText: Amazing, doable, stable and works as intended!Way better than previous generation that I'm upgradibg from.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great budget processor
reviews.reviewText: This is a Zen2 processor for AM4 socket motherboards. It was an upgrade (along with motherboard), replacing an A8-7600 which would have worked fine if Microsoft hadn't killed Dual Graphics when they killed Win7...anyway, it's also quite a bit faster than my Ryzen 5-2400G was, though the clock rate doesn't show it. I'd recommend this for gaming IF you could assign more than 2Gb of dedicated GPU RAM but you can't, that I'm aware of. This processor will handle moderate gaming on Low to Medium settings depending on the game, just don't expect to run Starfield with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 6 core for a fantastic price
reviews.reviewText: I was waiting for a 6core CPU with this performance profile under $100. This is it. If you must this thing runs the latest games just fine. I got it for a server, though. While I'd love to limit it to 35W if you need compute it goes up to 65 (80 system power). But it masters it all. Perfect home server CPU if you want some grunt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for Budget PC
reviews.reviewText: Pros- If you're wanting to run a 1080p/1440p gaming build this is your CPU, look no further- Runs cool with the Be Quiet! CPU cooler, stays below 30C with it on stock settings- Is overclockable to 4.2 out of the box, I changed it straight to 4.2 without adjusting voltage, or the BIOS did it for me, and it has no issues; but definitely runs 15% faster than it did. With the overclock it still remains under 45C during stress tests and intense gaming sessions, so it's doing it's job phenomenally- Integrated Graphics Card is nice for running a second monitor during gaming sessionsCons- Default CPU Cooler is trash, I wouldn't use it for gaming; it takes up a ton of space and especially where it counts by scaling horizontally right off the start which inhibits access or airflow to things on the board.Overall- I'd buy again, if you're spending more than $300 on a GPU then do yourself a favor and get a better CPU. This isn't going to run your GPU or other components well if it's the cheapest component in your build by a mile. But for a Budget Gaming Build running something along the lines of a AMD RX 6600 you'll be golden

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Perfectly adequate on a budget, but Ryzens w/iGPUs are generally PCIe 3.0!!!
reviews.reviewText: Cheapness, XMP capabilities, low power usage, and having a bundled cooler (assuming no overclocking) are its most positive aspects, but keep in mind this CPU uses PCIe 3.0 lanes! This will not matter in most use cases except playing the most recent gaming titles at max settings, but you shouldn't be getting this CPU in the 1st place if that's your goal. Has served me perfectly fine so far, but I recommend a 5600 (non-G) or even a 3600 over this to avoid any PCIe version bottlenecking in the future (e.g. using newer low-end graphics cards that use PCIe 4.0x4 lanes like the 6500 XT).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Runs great! Great value for the money.

reviews.reviewTitle: Excelente si lo quieres para empezar a jugar
reviews.reviewText: Es lo mismo casi casi que el 5600g, vino en condiciones perfectas, mucha seguridad en el envío, por lo menos fue mi caso, encendio todo bien y hasta ahora los juegos que me aguanta son (Apex, Wazone, Dead by daylight, Ghostwire tokio, Red Dead, Fortnite y Cyberpunk) esto hablando en los juegos que yo personalmente probé a los gráficos mas bajos obviamente, es bastante disfrutable y no se va a ver pixelado como doom, tranquilo, solo ajusta al bajo las texturas en ese tipo de juegos pesados, los demas tipo Valorant, Csgo, Gtav, van de sobra por eso no los mencionó, pero es un punto de referencia bueno para saber mas o menos que puedes jugar, trata de cuidarlo y ponerle buenos componentes también, no le vallas a exigir tanto 😦

reviews.reviewTitle: Roda jogos de PS 3 no máximo
reviews.reviewText: Roda até jogos de PS 4 mas com qualidade baixa e resolução baixa também. Me surpreendeu o quanto é potente esse vídeo onboard. Processador vale muito a pena para quem não pode ou não quer gastar com placa de video. Roda muita coisa boa e com gráafico bom. Recomendo.

reviews.reviewTitle: Perfect budget cpu with built in graphics
reviews.reviewText: Needed this part for a pc build

This processor is a beast in budget. 6 cores and 12 threads are more than enough for work. It can handle any load we throw at it. Integrated graphics is a plus that saves few thousands of a graphic card. Coming out to be a win win situation.
